  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Central retinal vein occlusion is a leading cause of severe visual impairment. Until now, no
      treatment has been available to improve visual acuity. The present study intends to
      investigate if intravitreal bevacizumab can improve visual acuity as compared to sham-treated
      control patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
